UNITED
AIR LINES
19CCI
FLIES MORE PASSENGERS
MORE PLANES - MORE
MAIL— MORE MILES THAN
ANY OTHER LINE IN
THE WORLD
* NEW YORK-CHICAGO-PACIFIC COAST ROUTE
* PACIFIC COAST ROUTE - CANADA TO MEXICO
* SERVICE TO 16 STATES

here's a reason why United flies more passengers, more
planes and more miles than any other line in the world
U
NITED
flies
more passenger
miles than all the commercial
air lines of England, France,
Germany combined! Each 24 hours
the planes of this one
line cover
40,000 miles. Every United plane is a
large twin-engined 3-mile-a-minute
Boeing, completely equipped with
the most modern aids to flying.
United's pilots average 4500 hours
in the air — well over half a million
miles apiece. The stewardess, in ad-
dition to being an attractive hostess,
is a registered nurse. Mothers with
babies and small children, or elderly
people who find ordinary kinds of
travel strenuous are particularly ap-
preciative of the stewardess service
on United planes.
Every plane is constantly in touch
with landing fields along the route
by two-way radio telephone. There
are
nearly 1400
United Air
Line
employees.
On a single Coast-to-
Coast flight scores of airplane and
engine experts,
radio dispatchers,
weather observers, airway caretakers,
instrument specialists, technicians
and
other
experienced
personnel
check and double-check the progress
of the planes.
Today thousands of people in all
parts of the country are using this
pioneer air service as a better and
more modern way to travel. Business
men "commute"
to cities three or
four hundred miles away. Vacation
ists use the air lines to save as much
as four or five days out of a two-weeks'
holiday. Fares are so reasonable now-
a-days that almost everyone can afford
the luxury and speed of plane-travel.
